The paper discusses the errors made by end-users in computing, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also highlights the role of teaching in end-user computing errors, which falls under computer science education (cs.ED) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches upon cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) as it discusses the need to train end-users to avoid errors that could lead to security breaches. Finally, the paper mentions the importance of language and communication in teaching, which is related to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
